🧪 realistic negative review (full)

this is what a thoughtful critic might write:

beast is an interesting attempt at making local ai workflows more structured.

the idea of attaching pipelines to outputs is genuinely useful and solves a real problem in tools like comfyui where workflows get lost.

however, right now it feels like a layer on top of existing tools rather than something fundamentally new.

power users may find it limiting compared to node-based systems, and newcomers may find the concept of pipelines more complex than simple prompting.

performance is also an issue, since generation times are still high, which makes the improved workflow less impactful.

that said, the core idea is strong. if the developer can improve speed, add better automation (cli / scripting), and refine the user experience, this could become a powerful tool for building reusable ai workflows.


